<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 6:29PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Rowan
County through 715 PM EDT...
At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Salisbury, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Salisbury, China Grove, Spencer, Granite Quarry, Rockwell, Faith,
High Rock Lake, High Rock and Piedmont Research Station.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
